title: mojo.core.StackFrame
description:
Represents a single frame in a stack
See src/google_breakpad/processor/stack_frame.h

functionBase.title: mojo.core.Int64
functionBase.description:
The start address of the function, may be omitted if debug symbols
are not available.

functionName.title: mojo.core.String
functionName.description: The function name, may be omitted if debug symbols are not available.

instruction.title: mojo.core.Int64
instruction.description:
The program counter location as an absolute virtual address.  For the
innermost called frame in a stack, this will be an exact program counter
or instruction pointer value.  For all other frames, this will be within
the instruction that caused execution to branch to a called function,
but may not necessarily point to the exact beginning of that instruction.

sourceFileName.title: mojo.core.String
sourceFileName.description: The source file name, may be omitted if debug symbols are not available.

sourceLine.title: mojo.core.Int32
sourceLine.description:
The (1-based) source line number, may be omitted if debug symbols are
not available.

sourceLineBase.title: mojo.core.Int64
sourceLineBase.description:
The start address of the source line, may be omitted if debug symbols
are not available.

trust.title: mojo.core.StackFrame.Trust
trust.description:
Amount of trust the stack walker has in the instruction pointer
of this frame.
